<br>
I had 157 FR battling the ranger, and was able to take him down with a single ro's debuff and 3 scoriaes.<br>
<br>
I had 135 MR battling the enchanter, he went down with the same Ro's debuff but just 2 scoriaes, I resisted 4 charms.<br>
<br>
I took out both warriors by creative stacking of buffs, and having my thorns as the last buff.  Even with disc, each warrior was killed with less than 4 nukes and 1 debuff of ro's, although I had to run away on each one and heal myself once.<br>
<br>
What I have noticed is that our DS is HIGHLY effective against all melee classes, as at 56 our DS with Bladecoat is 30pts each hit.  In addition, our debuff spell is one kick ass debuff and makes our nukes really effective.  <br>
<br>
Conclusion: A properly prepared druid in a duel situation is one tuff cookie to beat. <p><a href="http://worldzone.net/"target="web"><img src="http://worldzone.net/themes/azyn//sig2.GIF"border="0"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uainalda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ainalda</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/31/01 12:09:52 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.aredhel.ch/eq/atk.jpg width=103 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Observations from a 56 Druid on a NON-PVP server </span><hr size=1> The only fight I lost so far was vs a level 60 Paladin with 150+ MR <p><table width="489" border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
